race.comment: STARINION (12) led and dug deep under pressure but just failed to hold on when resuming over this course and distance 20 days ago. The winner on that occasion was beaten narrowly at Canterbury last Friday night so the form stacks up. Big chance to go one better. YOUR NOT THE BOSS (7) tackled the $50k Bega Sprint at the Sapphire Coast last time out, flashing home to get up for fourth. Well in after the claim and won't find this any harder. Not a prolific winner but this sets up nicely. PRETTY TAVI (11) has been kept fresh since a decent return over 1250m at Canterbury a month ago. Should be thereabouts again. KING CHARLES (4) has been in work forever. Often runs well when you least expect it. One for the exotics. GREYT THINKER (3) won a recent trial here on his home track and looks ready for a positive return from a 15-week spell.
